<p>Shellfish toxin warning for Bay of Plenty</p>
<p>The Waikato District Health Board has issued a warning about a potentially fatal shellfish toxin affecting the Bay of Plenty.</p>
<p>Toxins that cause Paralytic Shellfish Poisoning (PSP) have reached warning levels along the coast from Tairua to the Whakatane Heads, Matakana and Motiti islands.</p>
<p>The board says bivalve shellfish, catseyes and kina should not be taken or eaten, while paua, crayfish and crabs should have the guts removed before cooking.</p>
<p>The DHB says in severe cases, PSP can cause paralysis and respiratory failure.</p>
<p>Monitoring of toxin levels will continue in the affected areas.</p>
